text RustboroCity_PokemonSchool_Text_ExplainPoison {
    format("If a POKéMON is poisoned, it will steadily lose HP.\p The effects of poison remain after a battle.\p A poisoned POKéMON's HP will drop while it is traveling.\p Heal a poisoning using an ANTIDOTE.")
}

text RustboroCity_PokemonSchool_Text_ExplainParalysis {
    format("If a POKéMON becomes paralyzed, its SPEED drops.\p It may also not be able to move while it is in battle.\p Paralysis remains after battle. Cure it using a PARLYZ HEAL.")
}

text RustboroCity_PokemonSchool_Text_ExplainSleep {
    format("If a POKéMON falls asleep, it will be unable to attack.\p A POKéMON may wake up on its own, but if a battle ends while it is\l sleeping, it will stay asleep.\p Wake it up using an AWAKENING.")
}

text RustboroCity_PokemonSchool_Text_ExplainBurn {
    format("A burn reduces ATTACK power, and it steadily reduces the victim's HP.\p A burn lingers after battle. Cure a burn using a BURN HEAL.")
}

text RustboroCity_PokemonSchool_Text_ExplainFreeze {
    format("If a POKéMON is frozen, it becomes completely helpless.\p It will remain frozen after battle. Thaw it out using an ICE HEAL.")
}

text RustboroCity_PokemonSchool_Text_StudentsWhoDontStudyGetQuickClaw {
